The evidence with the title 'Remarks by the president at the Associated Press luncheon ... ' says Apr 3, 2012  ... The net result is that our country will end up spending more on health care , and the only reason the government will save any money -- it won't be on our books -- is because we've shifted it to seniors. They'll bear more of the costs themselves. It's a bad idea, and it will ultimately end Medicare as we know it. 
